      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FORCE FULL (8) has been racing well in the city without winning. Solid in fifth after racing parked last Saturday and had placed in his previous two outings. Draws wide but strikes at 50 per cent at this circuit and distance so looks well placed. MONTALBANO (9) is another that has been going around at Menangle and overcame a wide barrier to win there two back. JALANEEL (6) was down the track last time but was runner-up at Menangle at the previous appearance and came from this barrier to place the last time he raced outside of the city. I BET YOU (3) can give a sight again after he led from this barrier in a last-start win by 3.3 metres at Penrith.",
